<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1171.104142.figure1>
    dc:description "Figure 1. Phylogeny of Novochares spp. Part 1: Novochares punctatostriatus, Novochares tectiformis, Novochares sallaei, Novochares orchis, Novochares minor, and Novochares garfo species groups. Inferred from COI and 28 S combined sequence data. Numbers next to taxon names are extraction numbers (see Table 1). The Novochares portion of the phylogeny of Acidocerinae based on five gene fragments as presented in Short et al. (2021) is reproduced in the lower left corner for comparative purposes." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/881168" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1171.104142.figure17>
    dc:description "Figure 17. Dorsal habitus of Novochares spp. A N. guadelupensis B N. pichilingue C N. cochlearis D N. quadrispinus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/881184" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1171.104142.figure18>
    dc:description "Figure 18. Aedeagi of the Novochares sallaei species group A, B N. bisinuatus C-E N. yanomami F-I N. fernandezae J, K N. unguis L N. clavieri M-P N. cochlearis A, C, F, J, L, M, O, P dorsal view B, H, N lateral view D, G ventral view E, I, K oblique view M, N Brazil O Venezuela P Suriname." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/881185" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1171.104142.figure22>
    dc:description "Figure 22. Distribution of Novochares sallaei species group A N. cochlearis (red: circles, examined specimens; squares, literature / unconfirmed records), N. dicranospathus (yellow), N. pastinum (blue) B N. atratus (red: circles, examined specimens; squares, literature / unconfirmed records), N. clavieri (yellow), N. bisinuatus (blue), N. garciai (green) C N. chaquensis (red: circles, examined specimens; squares, literature / unconfirmed records), N. pichilingue (yellow) D N. fernandezae (red), N. tridentis (yellow), N. quadrispinus (blue), N. unguis (green)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/881189" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1171.104142.figure6>
    dc:description "Figure 6. Morphological features of Novochares spp. A, B mesoventrite C, D dorsal view of the head A N. tectiformis B N. cochlearis C Aulonochares ligulatus D N. pertusus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/881173" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

